definition:
Someone descended from Sheba who was a man of the Cushites living at the time of the Patriarchs, first mentioned at Gen.10.7; 
 son of: Raamah (H7484); 
 brother of: Dedan (H1719B); also called Sabean at Job.1.15; 3x
Group of she.va (שְׁבָא "Sheba" H7614) 
 § Sabeans = "drunkard" or "he who is coming"
 the people of the nation of Sheba
